-- Marks & Spencer Targets Sales of as Much as 12.5 Billion Pounds by 2014
-- B y   C e l e s t e   P e r r i
-- 2010-11-09T07:13:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-09/marks-spencer-plans-increase-in-sales-of-as-much-as-20-billion-by-2014.html
Marks & Spencer Group Plc targets
sales of as much as 12.5 billion pounds ($20.1 billion) by
fiscal 2014 as the company sells more online in the U.K. and
abroad.  The company targets multi-channel revenue of as much as 1
billion pounds by that date, it said in a statement distributed
by Regulatory News Service today. Revenue for its international
business, excluding Ireland, should also total as much as 1
billion pounds, the company said.  Marks & Spencer will also accelerate its Project 2020
savings plan and lifted the target by 50 million pounds to 300
million pounds, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at 
 cperri@bloomberg.net  